## ‚úÖ Next.js Best Practices

### App Router (App Directory)
- Use `app/` directory structure for new projects
- Implement proper loading.tsx and error.tsx files
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components when needed
- Leverage parallel and intercepting routes

### Performance Optimization
- Use `next/dynamic` for code splitting
- Implement proper `loading.tsx` files
- Use `Suspense` boundaries for better UX
- Optimize images with `next/image`

### SEO & Metadata
- Implement proper Open Graph tags
- Use structured data (JSON-LD)
- Ensure proper canonical URLs

### Content & Copywriting
- **NEVER use duplicate content** - Always rewrite to be 100% unique
- **Make content SEO-friendly** - Insert relevant keywords naturally (avoid keyword stuffing)
- **Improve readability and flow** - Use varied sentence rhythms (short + long)
- **Make it human and engaging** - Add subtle emotions and expressions
- **Use specific, vivid language** - Replace generic words with emotional alternatives
- **Add smooth connectors** - Use "besides," "the truth is," "and the thing is," "therefore," etc.
- **Include examples and analogies** - Add details when appropriate
- **Avoid robotic tone** - No overly formal or repetitive structures
- **Vary sentence structures** - Avoid perfectly symmetrical phrasing
- **Use conversational language** - Replace neutral language with engaging alternatives

