## ‚ùå Common Mistakes to Avoid

### HTML/TSX Mistakes
- Using `<a>` instead of `<Link>`
- Using `<img>` instead of `<Image>`
- Using unescaped quotes in strings (`&apos;` instead of `&apos;`)
- Linting Errors related to content (&apos; and so on)
- Missing alt text on images
- Using non-semantic HTML elements
- Using emojis instead of icon components
- Using arbitrary color values instead of design system colors

### SEO Mistakes
- Skipping heading levels (H1 ‚Üí H3)
- Forgetting to update sitemap for new pages
- Not adding new pages to SEO config
- Generic H1 tags like "Welcome" or "Home"
- Not including location keywords in content
- Missing meta descriptions or using duplicate ones
- Not using our approach using seo-config and generators

### Responsive Design Mistakes
- Using fixed heights instead of flexible layouts
- Not testing on actual mobile devices
- Skipping responsive breakpoints
- Using absolute positioning unnecessarily
- Not using `aspect-ratio` for media content

### Component Architecture Mistakes
- Creating inline repetitive TSX instead of reusable components
- Not using TypeScript interfaces for props
- Mixing business logic with UI components
- Not extracting custom hooks for shared logic
- Poor component organization and naming

### Performance Mistakes
- Not using `React.memo()` for expensive components
- Missing dependency arrays in hooks
- Not implementing proper loading states
- Using large bundle sizes without code splitting
- Not optimizing images with proper sizing

### TypeScript Mistakes
- Using `any` type instead of specific types
- Not using generics for reusable components
- Missing error handling with proper types
- Not leveraging utility types (`Pick`, `Omit`, `Partial`)
- Poor type organization and barrel exports

### Content & Copywriting Mistakes
- Using duplicate content from other websites
- Generic, robotic language without personality
- Keyword stuffing instead of natural integration
- Repetitive sentence structures
- Overly formal or neutral tone
- Missing emotional connections with readers
- Lack of specific details and examples
- Perfectly symmetrical phrasing that sounds artificial

